    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-07-28T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-07-28T08:00:00-05:00" n="132"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d132">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15 a 1/494: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chairman of the American Delegation</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-07-28T14:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 28, 1927—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 28—10:05 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>122. This morning Bridgeman called and, although he did not reveal full details
                    of the new British proposals, he did not indicate that any substantial change
                    had been made in the previous British insistence on small cruisers and armament
                    of 6-inch guns. The delegates of the three powers are having a meeting this
                    afternoon.</p>
                <p>We consider it extremely unlikely, in view of the foregoing, that a break-down
                    can be avoided, and this afternoon shall telegraph a <pb facs="0223" n="137"
                        xml:id="pg_137"/> general outline of our proposed statement for the final
                    plenary session. We shall insist that sufficient time be allowed us before
                    plenary session in order to communicate fully with you and to receive your final
                    instructions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gibson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
